* Iron Raptor continued to walk along with Prowl, still holding the small 
kitten to her chest.
She cought the stray thoughts from Prowl about the time that they had spent 
in her quarters, remembering it also but not thinking of it as such a big 
deal.
She felt a strain of regret as well just then.
She actually wished that what had happened in that room would have never 
happened at that time, that things had gone too fast and they were just 
acting on their sparks and not their brains.
But it wasn't like anything too much really had happened, the battle had 
called before they could really get into it.
But now she had her mind in the right place and did regret letting their 
relationship go too fast, remembering now to go slower so that there would 
be no more regrets.
Besides, they haven't even had a first date yet.
Iron Raptor sighed and looked down at the small kitten, not seeing Prowl 
smile at her.*

< I'll hear it later.>

*************************************************  ^..^

* Iris looked over the battle fieled before turning and heading in towards 
the CF, glancing up and seeing Prowl with Iron Raptor.
It was hard to explain but she knew that those two weren't in for the best 
of times and would be tested beyone imagination.
Iris crossed her arms, her face hidden behind her helm.
She hadn't been left active to just watch them, but she would let them be 
for now.
If only they knew....*
